<config xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:magento:module:Magento_Config:etc/system_file.xsd">
    <system>
        <tab id="byte8" translate="label" sortOrder="1010">
            <label>Byte8</label>
        </tab>
        <section id="byte8_stock_radar" translate="label" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
            <label>Stock Radar</label>
            <tab>byte8</tab>
            <resource>Byte8_StockRadar::config</resource>
            <group id="activation" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="5" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                <label>Activation</label>
                <comment><![CDATA[The module ships free and open-source on Packagist. To activate it, get a free activation key at <a href="https://byte8.io/activate/stock-radar" target="_blank">byte8.io/activate/stock-radar</a> and paste it below. Without a key, subscribe + dispatch flows are silently skipped.]]></comment>
                <field id="key" translate="label comment" type="obscure" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Activation Key</label>
                    <backend_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Backend\Encrypted</backend_model>
                    <comment><![CDATA[Format: <code>b8a_stk_<32 hex chars></code>. Stored encrypted via Magento's standard encryption.]]></comment>
                </field>
                <field id="endpoint" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Verify Endpoint</label>
                    <comment><![CDATA[Default <code>https://api.byte8.io/graphql</code>. Override only for staging / development.]]></comment>
                </field>
                <field id="timeout" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Verify Timeout (seconds)</label>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-greater-than-zero</validate>
                    <comment>Hard response timeout for the verify call. Default 5s. Verify fires at most once per 24h.</comment>
                </field>
                <field id="connect_timeout" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Verify Connect Timeout (seconds)</label>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-greater-than-zero</validate>
                    <comment>TCP/TLS connect timeout for the verify call. Default 2s.</comment>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="general" translate="label" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>General</label>
                <field id="active" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Enable</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="dispatch" translate="label" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Dispatch</label>
                <field id="throttle_minutes" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Throttle window (minutes)</label>
                    <comment>Notifications for a single product are spread randomly over this window so a restock doesn't blast all subscribers at once.</comment>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-zero-or-greater</validate>
                </field>
                <field id="expiry_days" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Subscription expiry (days)</label>
                    <comment>Pending subscriptions older than this are auto-cancelled. 0 disables expiry.</comment>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-zero-or-greater</validate>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="email" translate="label" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Email</label>
                <field id="sender" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Sender</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Email\Identity</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="template" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Template</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Email\Template</source_model>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="admin_alert" translate="label" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                <label>Admin alerts</label>
                <field id="threshold" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>High-demand subscriber threshold</label>
                    <comment>When pending subscriber count for any single product first crosses this number, alert the admin. 0 disables both transports below.</comment>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-zero-or-greater</validate>
                </field>
                <field id="bell_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Post to admin notification inbox</label>
                    <comment>When on, drops a message into the admin bell-icon inbox (top-right of the admin header).</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="email_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Send email to admin</label>
                    <comment>When on, sends a transactional email so the admin gets the alert outside the admin panel.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="recipient_email" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Admin recipient email</label>
                    <comment>Leave blank to use the General Contact email (Stores → Configuration → General → Store Email Addresses → General Contact).</comment>
                    <validate>validate-email</validate>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="email_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="email_sender" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="50" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Email sender</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Email\Identity</source_model>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="email_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="email_template" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="60" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="0">
                    <label>Email template</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Email\Template</source_model>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="email_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
            </group>
            <group id="security" translate="label comment" sortOrder="50" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                <label>Abuse protection</label>
                <comment>Each option is independent. Defaults ship the protections that have no UX cost; CAPTCHA and double opt-in are opt-in because they add friction.</comment>
                <field id="rate_limit_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="10" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Rate limit subscribe attempts</label>
                    <comment>Limits per-IP and per-email subscribe attempts. Recommended on.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="rate_limit_per_ip" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="20" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Max subscribes per IP / 5 min</label>
                    <comment>Default 5. Applies to both storefront and GraphQL.</comment>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-greater-than-zero</validate>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="rate_limit_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="rate_limit_per_email" translate="label comment" type="text" sortOrder="30" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Max subscribes per email / hour</label>
                    <comment>Default 3. Prevents one email from subscribing to many SKUs in a short window.</comment>
                    <validate>validate-digits validate-greater-than-zero</validate>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="rate_limit_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
                <field id="honeypot_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="40" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Honeypot field</label>
                    <comment>Adds a hidden form field that bots fill in. Zero UX cost. Recommended on.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="hide_created_flag" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="50" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Hide "already subscribed" hint in GraphQL</label>
                    <comment>When on, the byte8StockRadarSubscribe mutation always returns created=true, preventing email-enumeration probes. Recommended on.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="captcha_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="60" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Require CAPTCHA</label>
                    <comment>Uses Magento's built-in CAPTCHA (form id "byte8_stock_radar_subscribe"). Configure the CAPTCHA type in Customers → Customer Configuration → CAPTCHA.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="double_optin_enabled" translate="label comment" type="select" sortOrder="70" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Require double opt-in (email confirmation)</label>
                    <comment>Sends a confirmation email before the subscription becomes active. Adds friction but eliminates the "subscribe someone else" attack class.</comment>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Yesno</source_model>
                </field>
                <field id="confirmation_email_template" translate="label" type="select" sortOrder="80" showInDefault="1" showInWebsite="1" showInStore="1">
                    <label>Confirmation email template</label>
                    <source_model>Magento\Config\Model\Config\Source\Email\Template</source_model>
                    <depends>
                        <field id="double_optin_enabled">1</field>
                    </depends>
                </field>
            </group>
        </section>
    </system>
</config>
